
Usage: mekano <command> [options]

where <command> is one of:
    update, watch, status, clean, aliases, print, help

mekano help <term>     search for help on <term>
Commands can be abbreviated.

Options:

    -y, --shy                   Stops an update as soon as an error occurs.
    -n, --dry-run               No command is actually run.
    -f, --file <mekanofile>     Specify a different manifest. '-' for stdin.
    -r, --robot                 Parseable output.
    -v, --version               Output version and quit.

